The MariaDB container port `3306` will be mapped to a random free port on your host, also see [this section](https://java.testcontainers.org/features/networking/#exposing-container-ports-to-the-host) in the official Testcontainers docs regarding networking between host and container.

To access the port after the container has started, use the following methods:
``` Java
// access port
mariadb.getFirstMappedPort();

// get full JDBC URL
mariadb.getJDBCUrl();
```

Since you are using the `MariaDBContainer` module, you don&#39;t need to use 
`withExpostedPorts()`, it is already auto-configured.

Furthermore, I am unsure what you are trying to achieve here, you should remove this code:
```
mariadb.setPortBindings(Collections.singletonList(mariadb.getMappedPort(3306) +&quot;:3306&quot;));
```

For networking between containers, please check [this part](https://java.testcontainers.org/features/networking/#advanced-networking) of the docs.

