Considering you are passing a modified _array_ for each recursive _chain_ call, I&#39;d recommend creating a class.  
Here you can provide a dynamic list of values, to a set of recursive _chain_ calls.

```java
@SuppressWarnings({&quot;rawtypes&quot;, &quot;unchecked&quot;})
public Object chain(Object val, Function ... functions) {
    @SuppressWarnings(&quot;rawtypes, unchecked&quot;)
    class Chain {
        Object x;
        List&lt;Function&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

        Chain(Object x, Function ... functions) {
            this.x = x;
            list.addAll(List.of(functions));
            chain();
        }

        void chain() {
            x = list.get(0).apply(x);
            if (list.size() == 1) return;
            list.remove(0);
            chain();
        }

        Object get() {
            return x;
        }
    }
    return new Chain(val, functions).get();
}
