Usually you don&#39;t want just an `if` but an `else` clause as well.

    if(!(str instanceof String)) { /* do Something */ } 
    else { /* do something else */ }

can be written as

    if(str instanceof String) { /* do Something else */ } 
    else { /* do something */ }

Or you can write the code so you don&#39;t need to know if its a String or not. e.g.

    if(!(str instanceof String)) { str = str.toString(); } 

can be written as

    str = str.toString();

